The paper deals with lattice theory and matroids, which are topics commonly studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of closure operators and the Steinitz exchange axiom also suggest a connection to combinatorial optimization (cs.CO) and discrete structures (cs.DS). Finally, the study of M\"obius functions is a topic in algebraic combinatorics and graph theory (cs.GT).
